reviews.review_text: Awesome show still got my stub

Blow Away Blow away is not the greatest in the dead's many tunes, but some versions really take off, and this one does just that.  Seeing Brent on the DVD going full tilt boogie is really something, the guy had some soul that's for sure.

This is a great show, with many highlights, the Scarlet>Fire is tasty, the Rooster is nice too, I am not always a fan of it, but it sounds great here.

Also, this AUD sounds alright.  I revisited this show, had heard another AUD  source and wasn't that impressed, came back to see if another source was here and found this one, which I like.

So yeah, another killer show from the banner year of 1989.
